description:
Overview

Kick-Ass 2 is the second volume of Kick-Ass but is book three in the series (Hit-Girl being book two) created by writer Mark Millar and artist John Romita Jr.

History

Beginning in December of 2010 the series concluded with issue 7 in May 2012 spanning a 15 month run. Continuing the sporadic schedule of the first series, issues of this series were released between 1 and 5 months apart.

Plot

Set several months after the first book Mindy and Dave struggle to keep their identities as Hit-Girl and Kick-Ass a secret as she trains him to be a better hero. Meanwhile, Red Mist returns with a whole new attitude and a name change to match. Forming a group of villians he takes the game to the next level.

Collected in Kick-Ass 2.
name: Kick-Ass 2

description:
English translation of the Korean manhwa Very! Very! Sweet (Very! Very! 다이스키).

Korean Manhwa aimed at teenaged girls. From the same creative team that produced Chocolat. Very! Very! Sweet is a cute & energetic manhua in which character names are play on words & food-derived.

Cultural & emotional turmoil in in store for Japanese boy Tsuyoshi when his grandfather sends him to Korea to discover his ancient roots. There he is immediately confronted by brash neighbour Be-Ri who is in love with her older sister's boyfriend. The two slowly & awkwardly become friends, but with a language barrier & unrequited love-rivals between them, Be-Ri might never realise her true feelings for Tsuyoshi.
name: Very! Very! Sweet
